Setup: each trial draws FP64 Gaussian inputs, normalizes the matrix to Frobenius norm 1 and the vector to L2/Frobenius norm 1, rescales them to the requested constants, then casts those same inputs to each precision case.
Dims: 10000, 50000
Matrix Frobenius norms: 1, 224, 1000
Vector L2/Frobenius norms: 1
Trials per D: 5
Base seed: 12345
Rule of thumb for these random inputs: typical matrix entry is about matrix_norm / D, typical vector entry is about vector_norm / sqrt(D), and typical output entry is about matrix_norm * vector_norm / D.
renorm_rel is the relative L2 error after normalizing each output to the input-vector norm using FP32 for the normalization operation.
The separate normalization table compares each normalization precision against FP64-normalized ground truth. Rows with matmul_precision=fp64_ground_truth isolate normalization error.

